<div id="review_1366740896" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1366740896" />
    <a title="Angie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/30499852-angie"><img alt="Angie" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1399406856p2/30499852.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1366740896?book_show_action=true">Aug 17, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Angie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Angie" href="/user/show/30499852-angie">Angie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/25657858-love-after-pain">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1366740896" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3726360039669579840">You might want to have tissues ready before you start this book. In fact, this book should come with a box of tissues! Not going to lie, the blurb alone made me a little teary eyed. I started reading this book and could not stop. <br/><br/>The story is about David, a newly widowed father of seven year old Clare and newborn son Brody. The author, Torrie Robles takes you on an emotional rollercoaster of David&apos;s struggle to learn to live again after having the unimaginable happen. He is angry and has every r</span>
  <span id="freeText3726360039669579840" style="display:none">You might want to have tissues ready before you start this book. In fact, this book should come with a box of tissues! Not going to lie, the blurb alone made me a little teary eyed. I started reading this book and could not stop. <br /><br />The story is about David, a newly widowed father of seven year old Clare and newborn son Brody. The author, Torrie Robles takes you on an emotional rollercoaster of David's struggle to learn to live again after having the unimaginable happen. He is angry and has every right to be. You experience him going through all the stages of grief. You find yourself cheering him on in his journey, while at the same time, you just want to climb into the book and hold him when he has his bad days. He was a man that truly loved his wife and without her, he wasn't sure he could be the man he became because of her or the father he wanted to be. David had a huge support system from his parents and sister and found himself getting help from a new friend, Olivia who can relate to his struggles as she's a therapist and co-worker to David's sister. <br /><br />This is the first book I've read from this author and it won't be my last. It was beautifully written and just a beautiful story about lost love and learning to let go. There was so much emotion in this book. </span>
  <a data-text-id="3726360039669579840" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


