<div id="review_1371006383" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1371006383" />
    <a title="Pauline (Passionate About Books)" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/35116727-pauline-passionate-about-books"><img alt="Pauline (Passionate About Books)" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1562082957p2/35116727.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1371006383?book_show_action=true">Aug 22, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Pauline (Passionate About Books)" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Pauline (Passionate About Books)" href="/user/show/35116727-pauline-passionate-about-books">Pauline (Passionate About Books)</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/25657858-love-after-pain">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1371006383" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15935322217046814675">Finding the light...after so much darkness...<br/>A novel I just happened to stumble upon and I am forever grateful to have read such a beautiful story.This book ripped my heart open bit by bit...brought out so much pain,emotions,tears.Kept me interested till the very last sentence...and yet managed to put my heart back together.A story about loss and the stages of coping with such an ugly situation....trying to come out of it a survivor.Learning to control your life,even after such devastating event</span>
  <span id="freeText15935322217046814675" style="display:none">Finding the light...after so much darkness...<br />A novel I just happened to stumble upon and I am forever grateful to have read such a beautiful story.This book ripped my heart open bit by bit...brought out so much pain,emotions,tears.Kept me interested till the very last sentence...and yet managed to put my heart back together.A story about loss and the stages of coping with such an ugly situation....trying to come out of it a survivor.Learning to control your life,even after such devastating events...not simply existing.Yes...this book made me a blubbering mess but it also left a beautiful message which calmed my soul...everything does happen for a reason. 5 tear-stained stars for Torrie Robles and her exceptionally inspiring novel.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15935322217046814675" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


