<span id="freeTextContainer4606472280058157579">***ARC given on behalf of the author for an honest review **<br/><br/>I was recommended by a friend to read this book so i was excited to receive this book and she warned me that I would cry, but I had no idea I would through the whole book and that it would be a hard cry. Plus this book hit home for me , being the aunt of a nephew who lost his mother, my sister when he was 2. <br/>David has just lost his wife and isnow a single dad if two a 7 year old and a 2 month old. his life is over he lost his life, his </span>
  <span id="freeText4606472280058157579" style="display:none">***ARC given on behalf of the author for an honest review **<br /><br />I was recommended by a friend to read this book so i was excited to receive this book and she warned me that I would cry, but I had no idea I would through the whole book and that it would be a hard cry. Plus this book hit home for me , being the aunt of a nephew who lost his mother, my sister when he was 2. <br />David has just lost his wife and isnow a single dad if two a 7 year old and a 2 month old. his life is over he lost his life, his forever love how or will he ever make it. He has a great support group, his parents, his sister Destiny and her friend Olivia. Olivia is a ball buster, she helps destiny in group therapy, she pushes David's buttons but for good reason she's been where he is she understands loss. The more she's around the more David starts having feelings, feelings he feels guilty about, feelings that he's not sure of. He's crazy about Olivia, she's good with his children especially Clare he sees change in her but to David he's still married to Kate , will he ever be able to let go and love after the pain? omg I cried the whole time, ugly cry at that. I loved it.i loved how we were able to see how David and Kate met him much they loved each other and what thier dreams were. That was hard to know they had so much love, then for him to lose it. it was nice to see from his daughters view and his family, thus was truly a great written story that touched my heart and will stay with me forever. definitely a must read with a whole box of tissues. 5 stars easy.</span>
