<span id="freeTextContainer8694662434388717170">A friend of mine asked me if I would read this book and write a review in exchange for a free copy. She said that the latest copy with all of the editing changes were at the publishers so most of the small problems have been been addressed but there might still be a few typo&apos;s or spelling errors.<br/>Those types of errors are #1 on my pet peeve list when reading a book so I wanted to say no... but she read to me the description of the book and I had to have it!<br/>I just finished the book today. It was e</span>
  <span id="freeText8694662434388717170" style="display:none">A friend of mine asked me if I would read this book and write a review in exchange for a free copy. She said that the latest copy with all of the editing changes were at the publishers so most of the small problems have been been addressed but there might still be a few typo's or spelling errors.<br />Those types of errors are #1 on my pet peeve list when reading a book so I wanted to say no... but she read to me the description of the book and I had to have it!<br />I just finished the book today. It was everything she promised and more. I found hardly any errors - which pleased me.<br />It was a refreshing book that has written about well developed characters.<br />I loved the storyline... there are so many books out there where it ends up the mother alone raising the children... this book went the opposite direction with the big corporate lawyer trying to raise his kids while also trying to survive the guilt and grief of losing the love of his life. When he finds himself thinking about another woman he freaks out. I enjoyed going along for the ride as he figures out his life and the well-being of the children.<br />This is the first book I've read by this author, but I will definitely watch for more of her books.<br /><br /> **I received a free copy of this book in exchange for an honest review.**</span>
