        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1366693874" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9168206920707231079">I saw on facebook that a new author was giving away an arc of a book that was coming out and was looking for people to read it for an honest review so I thought ok I am always up for reading a new author. You never know when you will come across something you will fall in love with. Well that just happened with this book. I started reading it and found out that I couldn&apos;t put it down. I was hooked and had to keep reading to find out what was going to happen. I found myself yelling at David and O</span>
  <span id="freeText9168206920707231079" style="display:none">I saw on facebook that a new author was giving away an arc of a book that was coming out and was looking for people to read it for an honest review so I thought ok I am always up for reading a new author. You never know when you will come across something you will fall in love with. Well that just happened with this book. I started reading it and found out that I couldn't put it down. I was hooked and had to keep reading to find out what was going to happen. I found myself yelling at David and Olivia to get their head out of their butts and then crying because of the sorrow and grief controlling them. This is an emotional story about loss and grief and trying to find yourself after tragedy strikes and that sometimes we cant see what right in front of us. Torrie's writing is such that you can't help but root for them and feel all the sorrow, passion, anger and everything these two go through. She throws in some twist and turns and had me saying where did that come from. I loved this book and would highly recommend it. I will definately be looking to see what is next for Torrie because she has a new fan in me. </span>
  <a data-text-id="9168206920707231079" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
