<div id="review_1298896162" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1298896162" />
    <a title="Jennifer Lessard" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/29645667-jennifer-lessard"><img alt="Jennifer Lessard" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1556748149p2/29645667.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1298896162?book_show_action=true">Jun 04, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jennifer Lessard" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jennifer Lessard" href="/user/show/29645667-jennifer-lessard">Jennifer Lessard</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/25657858-love-after-pain">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1298896162" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17600056065139368050">Oh my, where do I begin....When I was asked to read Torrie Robles new book, Love After Pain, I jumped at the chance! I read Torrie&apos;s debut novel and thoroughly enjoyed it. Well, when I read the synopsis for this book it brought tears to my eyes. This story is very well written and the characters are well developed and extremely easy to relate to. Which is why I was sucked into the story right from the start. I didn&apos;t feel like I was reading a book I felt like I was living the story. Like this wa</span>
  <span id="freeText17600056065139368050" style="display:none">Oh my, where do I begin....When I was asked to read Torrie Robles new book, Love After Pain, I jumped at the chance! I read Torrie's debut novel and thoroughly enjoyed it. Well, when I read the synopsis for this book it brought tears to my eyes. This story is very well written and the characters are well developed and extremely easy to relate to. Which is why I was sucked into the story right from the start. I didn't feel like I was reading a book I felt like I was living the story. Like this was happening to a good friend which is why the tears fell. I think I experienced the stages of grief right along with David, Clare and the other family members. But like I told Torrie when I finished the book even after the anger and the tears, when I finished the book I was left with a feel good feeling that I love to feel after I have just finished reading an amazing book! For me, Love After Pain has earned a very well deserved 5 stars! I am truly looking forward to reading more from this author! Congratulations Torrie on a job well done!</span>
  <a data-text-id="17600056065139368050" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
