<span id="freeTextContainer8546648215591327331">I received an ARC in exchange for an honest review. <br/><br/>You should definitely have a box of tissues by your side while reading this book. It will take you on the emotional rollercoaster of a lifetime. The blurb totally sucks you in and breaks your heart before you even open up and start reading. <br/><br/>David goes through the most unimaginable pain that any man should ever have to go through when he sees his pregnant wife&apos;s life slip away before his eyes. Newly widowed, he has to deal with the grief over lo</span>
  <span id="freeText8546648215591327331" style="display:none">I received an ARC in exchange for an honest review. <br /><br />You should definitely have a box of tissues by your side while reading this book. It will take you on the emotional rollercoaster of a lifetime. The blurb totally sucks you in and breaks your heart before you even open up and start reading. <br /><br />David goes through the most unimaginable pain that any man should ever have to go through when he sees his pregnant wife's life slip away before his eyes. Newly widowed, he has to deal with the grief over losing his wife, while still trying to raise his seven year old daughter, Claire, and newborn son, Brody. He is filled with so much anger and hate at the world for taking his wife away from him and their children. You experience all the stages of grief right along with him: Denial, Anger, Bargaining, Depression, and finally, Acceptance. You definitely feel for this amazing man and want to hold him when he is depressed and cheer him on through his struggles to trying to accept and move on after such a devastating loss. David has had such a huge support system with his dad, mom, and sister, and he finds help from a new friend, Olivia, who can relate to his devastating loss and struggles, and who also happens to be a therapist and fellow co worker to his sister. <br /><br />This book will rip your heart open, but also put it back together piece by piece. This was a wonderful story of the grueling five stages of grief, finding acceptance and moving on, but most of all, being able to open your heart up and find love after such a devastating loss. This is the first book by Torrie Robles that I have read but it definitely won't be the last. I am really looking forward to reading more from her. </span>
