          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/25657858-love-after-pain">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1365667630" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer325747426466199449">This book was really, really good! Torrie Robles did an excellent job capturing the devastating emotions of a heart broken man. David has lost the love of his life in a tragic accident while she is pregnant with their son. After her death, he is left to raise their new born son and their young daughter. How will he get through this horrible tragedy? <br/><br/>Thankfully, David is surrounded by his wonderful family, including his parents and sister. They help him through this difficult time, and also help </span>
  <span id="freeText325747426466199449" style="display:none">This book was really, really good! Torrie Robles did an excellent job capturing the devastating emotions of a heart broken man. David has lost the love of his life in a tragic accident while she is pregnant with their son. After her death, he is left to raise their new born son and their young daughter. How will he get through this horrible tragedy? <br /><br />Thankfully, David is surrounded by his wonderful family, including his parents and sister. They help him through this difficult time, and also help him realize that there is life after pain, and love after pain. He meets Olivia, who has also suffered much tragedy in her life, through his sister. They had a connection, I could envision from the moment these two met. <br /><br />All I could think about while reading this book was how very lucky this man was to be surrounded by such loving, giving and caring people. They were so amazing, and helped him realize that he needed to move on with his life. Olivia played a HUGE part throughout his healing journey. I just adored her! What a firecracker! The two of them together! Wow! <br /><br />I felt many, many emotions throughout this book. Obviously the main feeling was sadness, but I found myself laughing quite a lot. The dialogue between David and Olivia had me in stitches. I especially enjoyed David's inner dialogue on several occasions. Great read, I would recommend this book and would definitely read more from Torrie Robles!</span>
  <a data-text-id="325747426466199449" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
