<div id="review_1382668475" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1382668475" />
    <a title="Carol" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/11107868-carol"><img alt="Carol" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1382668475?book_show_action=true">Sep 04, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Carol" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Carol" href="/user/show/11107868-carol">Carol</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/25657858-love-after-pain">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1382668475" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10812122053470166649">This was the first book that I have read from this author. When I read the synopsis I couldn&apos;t wait to read this story. Most of the time you see where it&apos;s the woman who loses her spouse and is left trying to raise her children alone. This is the first, that I have read, where its the man struggling to making without his wife. The author does a great job of conveying how he feels and what he is going through trying to cope with Kate gone. Trying to raise their 7 yr. old daughter and newborn son.</span>
  <span id="freeText10812122053470166649" style="display:none">This was the first book that I have read from this author. When I read the synopsis I couldn't wait to read this story. Most of the time you see where it's the woman who loses her spouse and is left trying to raise her children alone. This is the first, that I have read, where its the man struggling to making without his wife. The author does a great job of conveying how he feels and what he is going through trying to cope with Kate gone. Trying to raise their 7 yr. old daughter and newborn son. <br />What I didn't like was the fact that hardly anytime had passed and he is already attracted to another woman. Of course he pushes her away. Maybe it's just me, but if I was the spouse I would hope that my significant other didn't already replace me so soon. Makes you wonder how in love he really was. Also I wish the author wouldn't have used the cliche of having David call Olivia by his wife's name. So been over done everytime. I hate seeing in a book when the one left behind, as soon as they find someone, starts making it sound like the spouse they lost wasn't the one. <br />This wasn't a bad book and I would recommend reading it. It just hit my last nerve for someone who loved his wife he sure found things about the new love of his life that he didn't even think to do for his wife. Just my opinion.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10812122053470166649" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


