<span id="freeTextContainer11623107401909284684">I fell in love with this book from the beginning!! Although I did not let out physical tears this book tore me up. Its a heart wrenching, second chance at love kind of story. <br/><br/>David lost his wife and is now left with his daughter and newborn son to care for. He doesn&apos;t want to move on nor does he want to love again. But what he wants and what he and his kids need is a different story. <br/><br/>Olivia knows what David is going through. She has been through more pain than one should have to bear at any indi</span>
  <span id="freeText11623107401909284684" style="display:none">I fell in love with this book from the beginning!! Although I did not let out physical tears this book tore me up. Its a heart wrenching, second chance at love kind of story. <br /><br />David lost his wife and is now left with his daughter and newborn son to care for. He doesn't want to move on nor does he want to love again. But what he wants and what he and his kids need is a different story. <br /><br />Olivia knows what David is going through. She has been through more pain than one should have to bear at any individual time. <br /><br />Hearing both of their stories tore my heart open and I could feel the pain they were both going through. Olivia is like a breath of fresh air in David's gloomy world. Shes a short little thing but man can she hold her own and pack a punch with her words. She pushes David in things no one else would.<br /><br />Can David learn to handle his wife's death and allow Olivia in or will his second chance at love be lost because of his own stupidity? </span>
