  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1366146765" />
    <a title="MegL" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/23376502-megl"><img alt="MegL" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1468496820p2/23376502.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1366146765?book_show_action=true">Aug 17, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="MegL" class="user" itemprop="url" name="MegL" href="/user/show/23376502-megl">MegL</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/25657858-love-after-pain">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1366146765" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6489659938618020977">Love After Pain is a heartfelt, second chance love story. This was my first time reading Torrie Robles and I wasn&apos;t disappointed. Overall, the story was developed really well though there were a few errors. I was able to connect with David and Olivia. Their stories were absolutely heartbreaking. I could feel David&apos;s anguish through Torrie&apos;s writing and that&apos;s what really pulled me in. This is a story growth, strength and the ability to overcome unimaginable circumstances.</span>
  <span id="freeText6489659938618020977" style="display:none">Love After Pain is a heartfelt, second chance love story. This was my first time reading Torrie Robles and I wasn't disappointed. Overall, the story was developed really well though there were a few errors. I was able to connect with David and Olivia. Their stories were absolutely heartbreaking. I could feel David's anguish through Torrie's writing and that's what really pulled me in. This is a story growth, strength and the ability to overcome unimaginable circumstances.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6489659938618020977" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
